        "summaries": {
          "bn": "এই হাদিসে ইমাম সাদিক (আ.) নিশ্চিত করেন যে আল্লাহর সন্তুষ্টি ও অসন্তুষ্টি আছে, তবে তা সৃষ্টির আবেগ থেকে ভিন্ন।",
          "de": "In diesem Hadith bestätigt Imam al-Sadiq, dass Gott Wohlgefallen und Zorn hat, erklärt aber, dass diese Eigenschaften grundsätzlich anders sind als die Gefühle der Geschöpfe.",
          "en": "In this hadith, Muhammad ibn 'Ammara asks Imam al-Sadiq about whether God experiences pleasure and anger. The Imam confirms that God does indeed have pleasure (rida) and displeasure (sukht), but clarifies that these attributes are fundamentally different from the emotions found in creatures. God's anger is to be understood as His punishment, and His pleasure as His reward. This teaching reflects the Shia theological principle of tanzih (divine transcendence), affirming God's attributes while denying any anthropomorphic interpretation.",
